(819, 2, 'What is return type of getchar(), fgetc() and getc() ?', 'http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/g-fact-11/', 'geeksforgeeks.org', 'In C, return type of getchar(), fgetc() and getc() is int (not char). So it is recommended to assign the returned values of these functions to an integer type variable. Here is a version that uses integer to compare the value of getchar(). See this for more details.', ' C '),
