(850, 2, 'The OFFSETOF() macro,', 'http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/the-offsetof-macro/', 'geeksforgeeks.org', 'We know that the elements in a structure will be stored in sequential order of their declaration. How to extract the displacement of an element in a structure? We can make use of offsetof macro. Usually we call structure and union types (orÂ classes with trivial constructors) as plain old data (POD) types, which will beâ€¦ Read More &raquo;', ' C '),
(851, 2, 'Branch prediction macros in GCC', 'http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/branch-prediction-macros-in-gcc/', 'geeksforgeeks.org', 'One of the most used optimization techniques in the Linux kernel is &#8221; __builtin_expect&#8221;. When working with conditional code (if-else statements), we often know which branch is true and which is not. If compiler knows this information in advance, it can generate most optimized code. Let us see macro definition of &#8220;likely()&#8221; and &#8220;unlikely()&#8221; macrosâ€¦ Read More &raquo;', ' C '),
(852, 2, 'Diffference between #define and const in C?', 'http://geeksquiz.com/diffference-define-const-c/', 'geeksforgeeks.org', '#define is a preprocessor directive. Things defined by #define are replaced by the preprocessor before compilation begins. const variables are actual variables like other normal variable. The big advantage of const over #define is type checking. We can also have poitners to const varaibles, we can pass them around, typecast them and any other thingâ€¦ Read More &raquo;', ' C '),
(853, 2, 'A C Programming Language Puzzle', 'http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/a-c-puzzle/', 'geeksforgeeks.org', 'Give a = 12 and b = 36 write a C function/macro that returns 3612 without using arithmetic, strings and predefined functions. We strongly recommend you to minimize your browser and try this yourself first. Below is one solution that uses String Token-Pasting Operator (##) of C macros. For example, the expression &#8220;a##b&#8221; prints concatenationâ€¦ Read More &raquo;', ' C '),
(854, 2, 'What''s difference between header files "stdio.h" and "stdlib.h" ?', 'http://geeksquiz.com/whats-difference-between-and/', 'geeksforgeeks.org', 'These are two important header files used in C programming. While â€œ&lt;stdio.h&gt;â€ is header file for Standard Input Output, â€œ&lt;stdlib.h&gt;â€ is header file for Standard Library. One easy way to differentiate these two header files is that â€œ&lt;stdio.h&gt;â€ contains declaration of printf() and scanf() while â€œ&lt;stdlib.h&gt;â€ contains declaration of malloc() and free(). In that sense,â€¦ Read More &raquo;', ' C '),
(855, 2, 'How to print a variable name in C?', 'http://geeksquiz.com/how-to-print-a-variable-name-in-c/', 'geeksforgeeks.org', 'How to print and store a variable name in string variable? We strongly recommend you to minimize your browser and try this yourself first In C, thereâ€™s a # directive, also called â€˜Stringizing Operatorâ€™, which does this magic. Basically # directive converts its argument in a string. Output: MyVar We can also store variable nameâ€¦ Read More &raquo;', ' C '),
(856, 2, 'Introduction to Arrays in C Language', 'http://geeksquiz.com/arrays-in-c-language-set-1-introduction/', 'geeksforgeeks.org', 'An array is collection of items stored at continuous memory locations. The idea is to declare multiple items of same type together. Array declaration: In C, we can declare an array by specifying its and size or by initializing it or by both. Accessing Array Elements: Array elements are accessed by using an integer index.â€¦ Read More &raquo;', ' C '),
